name: Lynchburg Lemonadeol
description: Haskell features a type system with type inference and lazy evaluation. Its main implementation is the Glasgow Haskell Compiler. Messages can be sent to and received from ports, but these messages must obey the so-called "port protocol." Do you come here often? The syntax {D1,D2,...,Dn} denotes a tuple whose arguments are D1, D2, ... Dn.
